Similarly, human eyes perceive only a (narrower) portion of the EM radiation emitted by lamps
(approximately \humaneyesensitivity).
To quantify light energy (and exergy), we must move from broad-spectrum emitted EM energy~($\Phi$)
to light~($\dot{L}$). 
