Knowing that visual perception of light is a function of wavelength
leads to modifying Equation~\ref{eq:emissive_power}
to include a spectral weighting function~($f_\lambda$) such that
%
\begin{equation} \label{eq:weighted_emissive_power}
  \dot{L} = \int \Phi_{L,\lambda} \mathrm{d}\lambda = \int f_\lambda \Phi_{EM,\lambda} \mathrm{d}\lambda \; ,
\end{equation}
%
with $0 \le f_\lambda \le 1$
and $\Phi_{L,\lambda} = f_\lambda \Phi_\lambda$.

In Equation~\ref{eq:weighted_emissive_power}, 
the spectral weighting function~($f_\lambda$) converts 
